{"questionId":"25931","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A particle moves in a straight line such that its velocity, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo> </mo><mtext>m s</mtext><msup><mrow></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>, at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>t</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine when the particle changes its direction of motion.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognises the need to find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57079</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>57</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(s)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25931","referenceCode":"22M.2.SL.TZ2.6a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine when the particle changes its direction of motion.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maxim